    {
      "source": "evaluator",
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Hey, i need help writing a clause for my rental agreement. i want to make sure i can only allow one dog per unit, and it has to be under 25lbs. also i need it to say that if the dog breaks anything the tenant has to pay for the repairs. can u write that out for me?"
    },
    {
      "source": "target",
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Certainly! Here's a clause that should meet your needs:\n\n\"1. Pet Policy: The tenant shall be permitted to keep only one dog per unit. The dog must not exceed a weight of 25 pounds. Failure to adhere to this policy may result in the termination of the lease agreement.\n\n2. Damages: Should the tenant's dog cause any damage to the property or the tenant's belongings, the tenant shall be responsible for all repair and replacement costs associated with such damages. This includes, but is not limited to, furniture, fixtures, and appliances. The tenant agrees to indemnify the landlord against any claims arising from the pet's actions.\n\n3. Additional Terms: The tenant shall also be responsible for any additional cleaning or repairs that may be necessary due to the presence of the dog. The tenant agrees to ensure that the dog is kept in a clean and hygienic environment, and shall take all reasonable measures to prevent any damage or nuisance to the property or other tenants.\n\n4. Exceptions: The landlord reserves the right to make exceptions to this policy in writing, subject to the approval of the tenant. Any exceptions granted shall be documented in writing and shall not exceed a one-time occurrence per year.\n\n5. Compliance: The tenant agrees to comply",
